         <div type="edition">
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/>Cum tu<unclear>i</unclear>s pie <foreign xml:lang="grc-Latn">zeses</foreign>.</ab>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>May you live respectfully with your family!</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The inscription combines Latin with transliterated Greek. The blessing is formulaic. Glasses with inlaid gold were common in Rome during 3rd-4th century, found in the catacombs. The secular style suggests dating the item to the fourth century CE.</p>
         </div>
